Package com.eclipsesource.tabris.camera

Interface PhotoAlbum

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PhotoAlbumImpl
    public interface PhotoAlbum
extends org.eclipse.rap.rwt.client.service.ClientService

    The PhotoAlbum component can be used to receive pictures from a mobile client's photo album. The picture will be sent to the server side and a callback will be called. See PhotoAlbumListener. An instance of PhotoAlbum can be accessed using RWT.getClient().getService( PhotoAlbum.class ).

    Since:
    1.4
    See Also:
    PhotoAlbumListener, PhotoAlbumOptions, Client
    No Implement:
    This interface is not intended to be implemented by clients.

    • Method Detail

      • open

        void open​(PhotoAlbumOptions options)

        Instructs the client to open the photo album. The added PhotoAlbumListeners will be called when the user has selected a picture.

        Parameters:
        options - The options that should be used as the configuration for taking a picture. Must not be null.
